839
00:46:29.130 --> 00:46:32.400
She is sad and passionateat your highness' tent.

840
00:46:32.400 --> 00:46:34.930
And, by my faith, thisleague that we have made

841
00:46:34.930 --> 00:46:38.630
Will give her sadness verylittle cure.

842
00:46:39.100 --> 00:46:42.670
Brother of England, howmay we content

843
00:46:42.670 --> 00:46:45.600
This widow lady? In herright we came;

844
00:46:45.600 --> 00:46:48.270
Which we, God knows, haveturn'd another way,

845
00:46:48.270 --> 00:46:50.430
To our own vantage.

846
00:46:50.430 --> 00:46:52.430
We will heal up all;

847
00:46:52.430 --> 00:46:55.700
For we'll create youngArthur Duke of Bretagne

848
00:46:55.700 --> 00:46:59.630
And Earl of Richmond; andthis rich fair town

849
00:46:59.630 --> 00:47:02.770
We make him lord of. Callthe Lady Constance;

850
00:47:02.770 --> 00:47:04.330
Some speedy messenger bidher repair

851
00:47:04.330 --> 00:47:06.430
To our solemnity: I trustwe shall,

852
00:47:06.430 --> 00:47:08.530
If not fill up the measureof her will,

853
00:47:08.530 --> 00:47:10.670
Yet in some measuresatisfy her so

854
00:47:10.670 --> 00:47:14.530
That we shall stop herexclamation.

855
00:47:14.530 --> 00:47:16.130
Go we, as well as hastewill suffer us,

856
00:47:16.130 --> 00:47:20.630
To this unlook'd for,unprepared pomp.

857
00:47:40.870 --> 00:47:49.000
Mad world! mad kings! madcomposition!

858
00:47:49.000 --> 00:47:51.700
John, to stop Arthur'stitle in the whole,

859
00:47:51.700 --> 00:47:53.900
Hath willingly departedwith a part,

860
00:47:53.900 --> 00:47:57.530
And France, whose armourconscience buckled on,

861
00:47:57.530 --> 00:47:59.770
Whom zeal and charitybrought to the field

862
00:47:59.770 --> 00:48:03.100
As God's own soldier,rounded in the ear

863
00:48:03.100 --> 00:48:07.830
With that same purpose-changer,that sly devil,

864
00:48:07.830 --> 00:48:10.870
That broker, that stillbreaks the pate of faith,

865
00:48:10.870 --> 00:48:14.270
That daily break-vow, hethat wins of all,

866
00:48:14.270 --> 00:48:17.300
Of kings, of beggars, oldmen, young men, maids,

867
00:48:17.300 --> 00:48:18.900
Who, having no externalthing to lose

868
00:48:18.900 --> 00:48:21.600
But the word 'maid,' cheatsthe poor maid of that,

869
00:48:21.600 --> 00:48:30.800
That smooth-faced gentleman,tickling Commodity,

870
00:48:30.800 --> 00:48:36.470
Commodity, the bias of theworld,

871
00:48:36.470 --> 00:48:38.700
The world, who of itselfis balanced well,

872
00:48:38.700 --> 00:48:40.770
Made to run even upon evenground,

873
00:48:40.770 --> 00:48:44.600
Till this advantage, thisvile-drawing bias,

874
00:48:44.600 --> 00:48:48.130
This sway of motion, thisCommodity,

875
00:48:48.130 --> 00:48:49.870
Makes it take head fromall indifferency,

876
00:48:49.870 --> 00:48:53.570
From all direction,purpose, course, intent:

877
00:48:53.570 --> 00:48:55.830
And this same bias, thisCommodity,

878
00:48:55.830 --> 00:48:58.830
This bawd, this broker,this all-changing word,

879
00:48:58.830 --> 00:49:00.870
Clapp'd on the outward eyeof fickle France,

880
00:49:00.870 --> 00:49:02.430
Hath drawn him from hisown determined aid,

881
00:49:02.430 --> 00:49:04.600
From a resolved andhonourable war,

882
00:49:04.600 --> 00:49:09.070
To a most base andvile-concluded peace.

883
00:49:09.070 --> 00:49:09.870
(laughing)

884
00:49:09.870 --> 00:49:15.070
And why rail I on thisCommodity?

885
00:49:15.070 --> 00:49:18.700
But for because he hathnot woo'd me yet:

886
00:49:18.700 --> 00:49:20.370
Not that I have the powerto clutch my hand,

887
00:49:20.370 --> 00:49:23.670
When his fair angels wouldsalute my palm;

888
00:49:23.670 --> 00:49:27.970
But for that my hand, asunattempted yet,

889
00:49:27.970 --> 00:49:31.830
Like a poor beggar,raileth on the rich.

890
00:49:31.830 --> 00:49:36.070
Well, whiles I am abeggar, I will rail

891
00:49:36.070 --> 00:49:41.500
And say there is no sinbut to be rich;

892
00:49:41.500 --> 00:49:44.730
And being rich, my virtuethen will be

893
00:49:44.730 --> 00:49:48.270
To say there is no vicebut beggary.

894
00:49:48.270 --> 00:49:53.700
Since kings break faithupon commodity,

895
00:49:53.700 --> 00:50:00.230
Gain, be my lord, for Iwill worship thee.

896
00:50:01.430 --> 00:50:09.000


897
00:50:10.200 --> 00:50:18.930
Gone to be married! goneto swear a peace!

898
00:50:18.930 --> 00:50:27.270
False blood to false bloodjoin'd! gone to be friends!

899
00:50:27.270 --> 00:50:35.770
Shall Lewis have Blanch,and Blanch those provinces?

900
00:50:35.770 --> 00:50:40.070
It is not so; thou hastmisspoke, misheard:

901
00:50:40.070 --> 00:50:44.800
Be well advised, tell o'erthy tale again:

902
00:50:44.800 --> 00:50:48.800
It cannot be; thou dostbut say 'tis so:

903
00:50:48.800 --> 00:50:51.270
I trust I may not trustthee; for thy word

904
00:50:51.270 --> 00:50:53.270
Is but the vain breath ofa common man:

905
00:50:53.270 --> 00:50:55.270
Believe me, I do notbelieve thee, man;

906
00:50:55.270 --> 00:50:59.000
I have a king's oath tothe contrary.

907
00:50:59.000 --> 00:51:03.030
Thou shalt be punish'd forthus frighting me,

908
00:51:03.030 --> 00:51:06.670
For I am sick and capableof fears,

909
00:51:06.670 --> 00:51:10.630
Oppress'd with wrongs andtherefore full of fears,

910
00:51:10.630 --> 00:51:15.770
A widow, husbandless,subject to fears,

911
00:51:15.770 --> 00:51:19.100
A woman, naturally born tofears;

912
00:51:19.100 --> 00:51:21.700
And though thou now confessthou didst but jest,

913
00:51:21.700 --> 00:51:24.000
With my vex'd spirits Icannot take a truce,

914
00:51:24.000 --> 00:51:28.330
But they will quake andtremble all this day.

915
00:51:28.330 --> 00:51:33.070
What dost thou mean byshaking of thy head?

916
00:51:33.070 --> 00:51:38.530
Why dost thou look sosadly on my son?

917
00:51:38.530 --> 00:51:43.100
What means that hand uponthat breast of thine?

918
00:51:43.100 --> 00:51:45.330
Why holds thine eye thatlamentable rheum,

919
00:51:45.330 --> 00:51:50.030
Like a proud river peeringo'er his bounds?

920
00:51:50.030 --> 00:51:54.100
Be these sad signsconfirmers of thy words?

921
00:51:54.100 --> 00:51:59.170
Then speak again; not allthy former tale,

922
00:51:59.170 --> 00:52:05.830
